            <p>Never list your property before obtaining your STR registration number. Airbnb now requires valid registration numbers for Toronto listings and will remove non-compliant listings.</p>
          </div>

          <p>Success in Toronto's short term rental market requires more than just listing your property. Here are proven strategies we implement for our clients:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Optimize for Business Travelers:</strong> Toronto's Financial District generates consistent weekday demand. Equip your space with fast WiFi, a dedicated workspace, and business-friendly amenities.</li>
            <li><strong>Leverage Events:</strong> TIFF, Pride, Caribbean Carnival, and major sports events create surge pricing opportunities. Our <a href="/services/airbnb-dynamic-pricing-toronto">dynamic pricing system</a> automatically adjusts rates for these events.</li>
            <li><strong>Invest in Professional Photos:</strong> Listings with <a href="/services/airbnb-photography-toronto">professional photography</a> earn 20-30% more and book faster.</li>
            <li><strong>Response Time Matters:</strong> Airbnb's algorithm favors hosts who respond quickly. Our 9-minute average response time keeps your listing ranking high.</li>
            <li><strong>Cleanliness is Everything:</strong> One bad review about cleanliness can tank your listing. Our <a href="/services/airbnb-cleaning-toronto">professional cleaning teams</a> maintain 5-star standards.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="tip-box">
            <h4>üí° Tip #2: Consider Your Building's Rules</h4>
            <p>Many Toronto condos have their own STR restrictions beyond city bylaws. Check your condo corporation's rules before listing. We can help you navigate building-specific requirements.</p>
          </div>

